snippet.textDisplay: It's actually supposed to be Pabban Paar not Pa (Panjo Pe) or in English, on the tip of toes. I like Ali Sethi but It sounds as though he is collecting phlegm in the lower part of his front jaw in his parts which is kind of irksome to my ears... But overall I like the song, especially towards the end... it's like a change of story, somewhat tragic... Maybe the lyrics suggest she's calling to her beloved to find her through the sound of her bangles and fear that they will break and he won't be able to find her.... :'(  Nabeel Shaukat brings a certain emotion into the song. He sings with feeling and gives new meaning to words. I admire that about him.
